title: Two men jailed for suspected murders of 19 children and young women acquitted
description: An Indian court has acquitted two men suspected of murdering 19 children and young women 17 years ago due to a lack of evidence.

title: Families speak of fear after children taken hostage by Hamas | Stuart Ramsay
description: There is virtually nothing the families of the Hamas hostages can do but sit and wait for a phone call.

title: Rachel Riley condemns 'hideous' and 'unthinkable' Israel-Hamas war
description: Rachel Riley says it's difficult to witness the "hideous" Israel-Hamas war because - as a mother - her own children remind her of what's happening to families trapped inside the conflict.

title: Diana and Dodi Fayed seen in first-look images of The Crown's final series
description: Princess Diana's relationship with Dodi Fayed is among the storylines teased in the first images released of the final series of The Crown.

title: 'We have nothing': Doctor in Gaza hospital pleads for help as aid and electricity run low
description: A doctor in a Gaza hospital has begged for an end to the crisis in the region, warning they have been left with nothing for the thousands of people who have been admitted.

title: 'Impossible to know' how many Israeli hostages are still alive, says Hamas official
description: A Hamas official has told Sky News he "does not know" how many Israeli hostages are still alive.

title: Two people 'wearing football shirts' shot dead in Brussels -  reports
description: Two people have been shot dead in central Brussels, according to reports.

title: Voice notes from Palestinians | What we know about the 199 hostages
description: More than a week since the Hamas attack in Israel, thousands of Palestinians caught up in the conflict remain stuck in Gaza at its southern border with Egypt - as the threat of an Israeli ground invasion into northern Gaza looms.

title: Driver slapped with $1.4m speeding fine after going 35mph over limit
description: A motorist was handed a $1.4m (£1.1m) speeding fine after going 35mph over the limit  - and claims he was then threatened with court action unless he paid it.

title: Shipwrecks survey uncovers location of three Dunkirk boats
description: The wrecks of three boats used in the Dunkirk evacuation in the Second World War have been uncovered for the first time by a detailed survey of 30 shipwrecks off the coast of France.

title: What is the Rafah border crossing and who controls it?
description: At the southern tip of Gaza on the border with Egypt is the dusty and chaotic Rafah border crossing.

title: £1m worth of suspected cocaine found in wheelchair at airport
description: Officials at Hong Kong International Airport have uncovered 11kg of suspected cocaine hidden in the cushions of an electric wheelchair.

title: 'Too heavy' sumo wrestlers rejected from flights over weight concerns
description: An airline was forced to turn away a group of sumo wrestlers from two flights following concerns they would push the planes over their weight limit.

title: Poland's opposition leader Donald Tusk declares election victory
description: Polish opposition leader Donald Tusk is declaring the beginning of a new era after three opposition parties appeared to have won enough votes in Sunday’s election to oust the governing party.

title: Biden says Israeli occupation of Gaza would be 'a mistake' - as foreign nationals at border hope to escape
description: President Joe Biden has said the Hamas militant group should be eliminated, but warned it would be a mistake for Israel to occupy Gaza, calling instead for a "two-state solution".
